# Roadmap

Last updated: April 27, 2026.

This roadmap tracks current product and security priorities. `docs/audit.md` is still the detailed source of truth; this file is the short operational map.

## Phase A: Privacy And Data Lifecycle
- Landed baseline: support warnings, server-side sensitive-content rejection, lifecycle columns, hashed route logs, clear-all local data, sign-out cleanup, Settings privacy copy, and planning import/export guardrails.
- Remaining: local autosave setting, support retention/deletion execution, admin triage workflow, and a final cloud-sync policy for planning teacher notes.
- Keep user-facing privacy copy precise: "never stored" applies specifically to drafting raw notes and generated AI output, with explicit planning/support exceptions.

## Phase B: Support And Operations
- Landed baseline: server-side `app_admins` allowlist, `/admin/support` queue, status filters, assignment, redaction, soft deletion, and support operations runbook.
- Landed follow-up: sanitized support intake notifications through `OPS_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL` and dry-run-first support retention tooling.
- Keep raw support emails out of route logs and notifications; use request IDs, user IDs, hashes, or aggregate counters.
- Configure and test `OPS_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL` in deployed environments.
- Remaining: deployed alert validation, scheduled retention automation, abuse dashboard, and runbooks for AI provider failures, planning sync conflicts, account deletion, and release rollback.

## Phase C: Planning Sync Reliability
- Landed baseline: timestamp-only conflict detection has been replaced with server-generated revisions, conditional writes, server-owned `updated_at`, separate `client_updated_at`, and durable planning conflict audit rows.
- Landed client support: local storage/import/export and the replay queue now preserve revisions, conflict IDs, server timestamps, and resolution strategy.
- Landed operations support: `/admin/planning-sync` exposes conflict counts, unresolved/resolved filters, recent sync rows, and clock-drift signals without showing raw teacher notes.
- Remaining: browser-flow tests for offline/online resolution, deployed migration verification, alerting for conflict spikes, and the final cloud policy for teacher notes.
- Keep product copy honest: this is revisioned backup/sync, not collaboration-grade real-time editing.

## Phase D: AI Quality And Safety
- Landed baseline: `usage_events` now records AI provider/model, prompt version, output-guard version, guard pass/fail state, and non-content warning labels.
- Landed guardrail: `/api/ai` assembles generated text server-side, blocks obvious reintroduced identifiers or new person placeholders before returning output, and releases reserved quota on blocked output.
- Landed eval support: synthetic fixtures and tests cover prompt clauses, placeholder preservation, guard blocking, warning headers, and blocked-output usage metadata.
- Landed operations support: provider timeout/error classification, synthetic `pnpm ai:smoke`, and `/admin/ai-governance` for guard/version diagnostics without raw content.
- Remaining: expand the golden/red-team suite, wire the smoke test into release automation, add alerting for guard failure spikes, and add teacher feedback/report-without-content workflow.

## Phase E: Account And Security Maturity
- Landed baseline: confirmed email-change flow, authenticated account JSON export, admin-tracked account deletion requests, and `/admin/account-requests`.
- Landed security hardening: registration no longer returns the specific "already registered" message, `/admin` is middleware-protected, CSP now includes `frame-ancestors 'none'`, CSP report-only posts to `/api/csp-report`, and HSTS is set in production.
- Remaining: decide whether deletion can be automated for accounts without billing/retention blockers, add true session/device visibility or MFA if needed, add app-level auth throttling if Supabase controls are insufficient, move CSP toward nonce/hash enforcement, and complete manual accessibility/live auth-security sign-off.
